### YAML Format Specification

Return valid YAML with proper indentation and structure.

### Rules
- Use 2 spaces for indentation (no tabs).
- Root element is a mapping with page metadata.
- Use arrays for lists and repeated elements.
- Preserve exact text content including punctuation.
- Use descriptive keys for different content types.
- Include images as a list of objects with id and description.

### Example Output
```yaml
page: 1
title: "Document Title"
text_blocks:
  - id: t1
    type: heading
    content: "Section Header"
    font_size: 18
  - id: t2
    type: paragraph
    content: "This is the paragraph content."
tables:
  - id: tbl1
    headers: ["Column A", "Column B"]
    rows:
      - ["Data 1", "Data 2"]
      - ["Data 3", "Data 4"]
images:
  - id: "1.1img"
    description: "Company logo in top-right corner"
format: yaml